          "type": "richtext",
          "id": "tooltip_1_content",
          "label": "Tooltip 1 content",
          "default": "<p><strong>WHAT IS VOLCANIC ASH?</strong></p><p>Volcanic ash in textiles means ultra-fine mineral particles from volcanic rock. Embedded in fibers, they create microscopic pathways that help absorb and move moisture vapor away from the skin instead of letting it sit on the surface.</p><p><strong>WHY IS IT IN JAX SHEETS?</strong></p><p>Jax Sheets weave volcanic ash into the fabric so humidity is pulled away from your body before it can feel damp or clammy. That keeps the sleep surface drier and more breathable on warm or humid nights.</p>"
